Keenan Hayes is a professional rodeo cowboy from Hayden, Colorado, who has made a significant impact in the sport at a young age. He specializes in bareback riding and has set several records in the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA).

Here you can follow Keenan Hayes’ net worth, career earnings, biography, career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Keenan Hayes

Born and raised in Hayden, Colorado, Keenan Hayes is a 20-year-old cowboy who has been riding since he was nine years old. He grew up in a supportive community that has always been there to cheer him on, whether he’s competing in local rodeos or making his mark on the national stage.

Early Career

Hayes’ early career was marked by his determination and passion for rodeo. He started riding at a young age and gradually worked his way up from mutton-busting to calves, steers, and junior bulls.

His hard work and dedication paid off when he set the record for the most money earned on a PRCA permit in 2022.

Professional Career

Hayes joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2022 and quickly started setting records.

In his rookie year, Hayes won 16 rodeos and set a PRCA regular-season earnings record of $265,896.He also set a bareback riding regular-season earnings record.

Hayes won the Mountain States Circuit Finals, the 150th Silver Spurs Rodeo, and the Home Of Champions Rodeo. He also won the championship at the Ellensburg Rodeo, earning him the title “Mr. 100”.

Hayes has been recognized for his aggressive and strong riding style, which has earned him countless wins. He has more than 90 qualified rides and his 46 rides of 85 Points or More rank first in the PRCA.

Keenan Hayes’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Keenan Hayes’ net worth is estimated to be $2 million.

He has earned a significant amount through his rodeo career. His earnings for the year alone have exceeded $265,000.

Career Earnings

Throughout his career, Hayes has consistently been a high earner. In 2022, he set the record for most money earned on a PRCA permit, earning $81,128.

In 2023, he broke the single-season earnings record in bareback riding with $237,546.

Endorsements

Hayes has several endorsements, including Cinch Jeans, Rocky Mountain Rodeo, Fatty’s Smoked Meat Sticks, Skiver Boots, and Way Out West Trading Company.

Personal Details

Girlfriend

Bareback rider Keenan Hayes appears to be single. He is focused on his career.

How Old is Keenan Hayes?

As of 2023, Keenan Hayes is 20 years old.

How tall is he?

He is 5 ft 6 inches tall.

What is his nationality?

He is American.
